Why Renters Insurance Is Important

Many renters assume their landlord's insurance covers their belongingsâ€”it doesn't. Your landlord's policy only covers the building structure. Your personal possessions, from furniture to electronics to clothing, need their own protection.

Renters insurance is surprisingly affordable and provides essential coverage for your belongings, liability protection, and even additional living expenses if your rental becomes uninhabitable.

What Renters Insurance Covers

Personal Property

Protects your belongingsâ€”furniture, electronics, clothing, and moreâ€”from theft, fire, vandalism, and other covered perils.

Liability Coverage

Covers legal costs and damages if someone is injured in your rental or if you accidentally damage someone else's property.

Additional Living Expenses

Covers hotel and meal costs if your rental becomes uninhabitable due to a covered loss like fire or severe water damage.

Optional Coverage Enhancements

Scheduled Personal Property

Extra coverage for high-value items like jewelry, cameras, or musical instruments.

Water Backup Coverage

Protects against damage from sewer or drain backups.

Identity Theft Coverage

Helps cover expenses related to restoring your identity after theft.

Earthquake Coverage

Specialized protection for earthquake damage in applicable areas.

Pet Damage Coverage

Covers damage caused by your pets to the rental property.
